{
  "uuid": "dd31d5d0a83ce47ad10bddec6a0c0e14",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Executive",
  "description": "<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Project Management:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Oversee the entire project lifecycle, from initial planning and design interpretation to execution and final handover.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Client Relations:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Act as the main point of contact for clients, managing their expectations, communications, and satisfaction.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Team Coordination:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Liaise with designers, architects, and contractors to ensure project requirements are met and that everyone is working toward the same objectives.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Site Supervision:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Conduct regular site visits to ensure work conforms to specifications, quality standards, and design plans.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Budget and Schedule Management:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Prepare and manage project budgets and schedules, and report on progress to ensure timely and cost-effective completion.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Issue Resolution:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Address and resolve any on-site issues, potential risks, or discrepancies that arise during the project.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Procurement:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Manage the procurement of materials, fixtures, and equipment as needed for the project.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Qualifications and skills:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Education:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>A degree or diploma in Interior Design, Construction Management, Architecture, or a related field is often required.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Experience:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Minimum of 2-4 years of experience in project management, preferably in interior fit-out, commercial, or retail projects.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Technical Skills:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Proficiency in reading architectural and technical drawings (e.g., AutoCAD), and knowledge of construction methods are often necessary.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Soft Skills:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Strong communication, negotiation, and interpersonal skills are crucial for managing diverse stakeholders. Excellent organizational, time management, and problem-solving skills are also vital for multitasking and working under pressure.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Interested candidates, you may send your resume to admin@taishin.com.sg</p>\n<p>Application applicable for Singaporean and Malaysian candidates only.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>",
